12/01/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase said in a televised interview Saturday (10 January) that the country's accession to NATO would open a new chapter in the Romanian history. 
Accession would eliminate policy ambiguities that surfaced over the past three years and bolster foreign investments, he added.
In other news, leaders of the ruling Socialist Democratic Party are to meet Monday with President Ion Iliescu to present policy goals for the year. 
The forum is aimed at bridging differences in views expressed by government officials and the presidency. 
(Nine o'Clock - 12/01/04; TVR 1, Rompres - 10/01/04)
